'''拉维达斯河坛'''（Sant Ravidas Ghat，[[印地语|印地语]]: संत रविदास घाट）是[[瓦拉纳西|瓦拉纳西]]最南面也是最大的河坛<ref name="The Times of India 2013">{{cite web | title=Ganga Mahotsav venue shifts to Sant Ravidas Ghat | website=The Times of India | date=11 November 2013 | url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/city/varanasi/Ganga-Mahotsav-venue-shifts-to-Sant-Ravidas-Ghat/articleshow/25579072.cms | accessdate=20 October 2015 | archive-date=2020-08-19 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200819000757/https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/city/varanasi/Ganga-Mahotsav-venue-shifts-to-Sant-Ravidas-Ghat/articleshow/25579072.cms | dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=When some social groups decided to remove the silt in an area of 150 m between Assi and Ravidas Ghats along Ganga river in Varanasi, the tractor-trolleys were stopped by the local authorities on its way to Nagwa, where a space has been created to dump the garbage.|url=http://www.dailymail.co.uk/indiahome/indianews/article-3006830/LUCKNOW-MAIL-Tough-times-ahead-Mulayam-s-SP.html|accessdate=2017-01-01|archive-date=2017-01-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170108094417/http://www.dailymail.co.uk/indiahome/indianews/article-3006830/LUCKNOW-MAIL-Tough-times-ahead-Mulayam-s-SP.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>。这是一个拉维达希亚宗教的重要宗教场所，因拉维达斯信徒的宗教旅游而闻名<ref name="dainikbhaskar 2016">{{cite web | title=आज रविदास घाट पर होगा समाजसेवियों का सम्मान | website=dainikbhaskar | date=22 February 2016 | url=http://www.bhaskar.com/news/MP-UJJ-MAT-latest-ujjain-news-043447-3664142-NOR.html | language=hi | accessdate=27 February 2016 | archive-date=2019-10-29 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191029134829/https://www.bhaskar.com/news/MP-UJJ-MAT-latest-ujjain-news-043447-3664142-NOR.html | dead-url=no }}</ref>，有一个25英亩的公园<ref name="India Today 1997">{{cite web | title=In Varanasi, 25 acres are being acquired for a Sant Ravidas Park. | website=India Today | date=28 July 1997 | url=http://indiatoday.intoday.in/story/uttar-pradesh-exchequer-suffers-as-mayawati-splurges-on-statues-of-dalit-heroes/1/274579.html | accessdate=20 October 2015 | archive-date=2017-01-08 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170108185923/http://indiatoday.intoday.in/story/uttar-pradesh-exchequer-suffers-as-mayawati-splurges-on-statues-of-dalit-heroes/1/274579.html | dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name="Indian Express">{{cite web | title=The four went to Sant Ravidas Park and then to the Sant Ravidas ghat | website=Indian Express | url=http://archive.indianexpress.com/news/bhu-student-drowns-in-ganga-two-others-missing/690385/ | accessdate=20 October 2015 | archive-date=2016-11-27 | archive-url=https://archive.is/20161127101553/http://archive.indianexpress.com/news/bhu-student-drowns-in-ganga-two-others-missing/690385/ | dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name="The Times of India 2010">{{cite web | title=The sites from where samples were picked included Ravidas Park | website=The Times of India | date=21 May 2010 | url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/city/varanasi/Ganga-water-contaminated-with-heavy-metals/articleshow/5959877.cms | accessdate=20 October 2015 | archive-date=2020-03-06 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200306043539/https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/city/varanasi/Ganga-water-contaminated-with-heavy-metals/articleshow/5959877.cms | dead-url=no }}</ref>
。

拉维达斯河坛于2008年2月拉维达斯诞生631周年时宣布兴建<ref name="dna 2008">{{cite web | title=UP Chief Minister said she would provide Rs twenty crore to complete the construction of a ghat along the banks of the Ganga to be named after the 14th century saint Ravidas at Nagwa | website=dna | date=21 February 2008 | url=http://www.dnaindia.com/india/report-mayawati-claims-to-have-put-an-end-to-mulayam-s-oppressive-era-1152128 | accessdate=20 October 2015 | archive-date=2020-08-19 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200819000811/https://www.dnaindia.com/india/report-mayawati-claims-to-have-put-an-end-to-mulayam-s-oppressive-era-1152128 | dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name="Photogallery 2008">{{cite web | title=Uttar Pradesh Chief Minister Mayawati unveils the golden Palanquin, brought from Jalandhar, during her visit at Sant Ravidas Temple, in Varanasi on Thursday | website=Photogallery | date=22 February 2008 | url=http://photogallery.indiatimes.com/news/india/mayawati-at-varanasi/articleshow/2803618.cms | accessdate=24 April 2016 | archive-date=2019-10-29 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191029140332/https://photogallery.indiatimes.com/news/india/mayawati-at-varanasi/articleshow/2803618.cms | dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name="www.oneindia.com 2008">{{cite web | title=Maya's golden 'palki' reaches Varanasi | website=www.oneindia.com | date=20 February 2008 | url=http://www.oneindia.com/2008/02/20/mayas-golden-palki-reaches-varanasi-1203525204.html | accessdate=20 October 2015 | archive-date=2019-10-29 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191029134829/https://www.oneindia.com/2008/02/20/mayas-golden-palki-reaches-varanasi-1203525204.html | dead-url=no }}</ref>，2009年由首席部长Mayawati揭幕<ref name="Rai Bureau 2016">{{cite web | last=Rai | first=Manmohan | last2=Bureau | first2=ET | title=Mayawati government took steps to honour and highlight the role of Sant Ravidas, like renaming Bhadohi to Sant Ravidas Nagar, constructing a Ravidas Ghat and Park in Varanasi and installing his statue there, building a Ravidas College in Faizabad and constituting an award in his name | website=The Economic Times | date=22 February 2016 | url=http://economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/politics-and-nation/mayawati-slams-modi-sp-for-participation-in-sant-ravidas-jayanti-celebrations/articleshow/51089419.cms | accessdate=24 April 2016 | archive-date=2019-11-16 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191116162326/https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/politics-and-nation/mayawati-slams-modi-sp-for-participation-in-sant-ravidas-jayanti-celebrations/articleshow/51089419.cms | dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name="The Times of India 2009">{{cite web | title=Ravidas Ghat - Just a step away | website=The Times of India | date=2009-06-23 | url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/city/varanasi/Ravidas-Ghat-Just-a-step-away/articleshow/4693445.cms | accessdate=2015-10-20 | archive-date=2020-08-19 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200819000757/https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/city/varanasi/Ravidas-Ghat-Just-a-step-away/articleshow/4693445.cms | dead-url=no }}</ref>。

